{"url": "https://www.ejcancer.com/article/S0959-8049(18)30041-8/fulltext", "title": "Standard normoxic versus physiological hypoxic culture of AML patients' (pts) whole blood (WB) samples with immune modulatory kits yields comparable proportions of dendritic cells and functional results", "author": "F. Doraneh gard", "affli": "University Hospital of LMU, Department for Hematopoietic cell Transplantations, Med3, Munich, Germany", "session": "P02.09", "doi": "DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ejca.2018.01.027", "text": "\nBackground:\nFor a clinical treatment strategy DC\nleu\ncould be generated\nex vivo\nand transferred to the pts or alternatively blasts modulated to leukemia-derived DC (DC\nleu\n)\nin vivo\n-resulting in Tcell activation: Combinations of GM-CSF+ PICIBANIL (I), or +PGE2 (K) or + PGE1 (M)are kits that convert blasts into a \u2018DC\nleu\n-vaccine\u2019 and induce antileukemic T-cell(memory) without induction of blast proliferation in a WB-culture-model, in the presence of soluble and cellular components of the pt. To simulate physiological conditions most we compared normoxic (N*) standard- (21%0\n2\n) vs physiological hypoxic (H*) (10% O\n2\n) culture conditions.", "keywords": ""}
