{"url": "https://www.ejcancer.com/article/S0959-8049(18)30026-1/fulltext", "title": "Breast cancer immunotherapy using magnetised oncolytic viruses", "author": "H. AL-Janabi", "affli": "The University of Sheffield, Sheffield, United Kingdom", "session": "A8", "doi": "DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ejca.2018.01.012", "text": "\nBackground:\nOncolytic viruses (OV) are encouraging new immunotherapies for cancer. OVs induce immunogenic cell death (ICD) and activate antitumour immunity. However, clinical use has been limited to intratumoural delivery as a result of inadequate tumour targeting following systemic injection, strong anti-viral host immune responses and sequestration by the liver and spleen.", "keywords": ""}
