{"url": "https://www.ejcancer.com/article/S0959-8049(18)30022-4/fulltext", "title": "The adjuvant effect of melanin is superior to Incomplete Freund adjuvant in a tumor subunit vaccine model", "author": "A.F. Carpentier", "affli": "Hopital Saint Louis, AP/HP, Paris, France", "session": "Plenary Symposium 4: Anti-cancer vaccines;A4", "doi": "DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ejca.2018.01.008", "text": "\nBackground:\nWe recently reported that synthetic melanin bound to subunit vaccine antigens significantly enhances CD8+ T-cell responses in mice [1]. In an established tumor model, we compared this vaccine approach to the standard adjuvant formulation combining the Incomplete Freund Adjuvant (IFA) and a TLR9 agonist.", "keywords": ""}
